ALBERT B. COREY, Plaintiff, v. WALTER P. LONG, Defendant. Appeal from an order of Special Term, confirming report of a referee appointed to take and pass the accounts of a receiver.

Before Monell, Sedgwick, and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided February 1, 1873. C. W. Bangs, for plaintiff’s assignee. M. V. B. Bachman, for receiver. Order affirmed.

No opinion rendered.
